---

Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @Zucchini{1} and halve lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate half the @Ginger{1%thumb}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While zucchini cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @Ponzu Sauce{12%milliliters}, and @Soy Sauce{1%tablespoon} until smooth and no lumps remain. Whisk in @Pork Ramen Stock Concentrate{1}, @Plum Jam{1}, @Gochujang Sauce{1/2%ounce}, and @water{1/4%cup} until combined.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Pork{10%ounce}; season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until pork is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Stir in scallion whites, ginger, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining @Soy Sauce{1%tablespoon}, and @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon}. Cook until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in sauce. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{30-60%seconds}. Turn off heat.

Once water is boiling, add 3/4 of the @Ramen Noodles{6%ounce} to #pot{} (save the rest for another use). Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Drain; rinse thoroughly under cold water, ~{30%seconds}. (This stops the cooking and helps prevent sticky noodles.)

Add drained noodles, zucchini, and @Butter{1%tablespoon} to pan with pork mixture. Toss until noodles are warmed through and everything is combined. (TIP: If needed, stir in water a splash at a time until noodles are thoroughly coated in sauce.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide stir-fry between #bowls{}. Top with scallion greens and serve.